io.spine.validate

Interface ConstraintTranslator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the translation result

    public interface ConstraintTranslator<T>
    Translates validation constraints into an output form.

    The format of the output is implementation-dependant. For example, given message value, a translator may perform validation and output any found violations. Another example would be printing validation code in a target language (e.g. Java).

    A instance of ConstraintTranslator should only be used for a single type of messages. A translator need not be thread-safe. An instance of translator is, most likely, a mutable object. If any resources must be closed when finishing the translation job, translate() is the right place to do so.
